June first:
Enid, dearest girlie:
It seems almost too good to be true, that I am to see you so soon. Of course everything is for the best - and you are coming home to the very best and finest and dearest Daddy in all the world - and all the rest of us as you know are so very happy that you are to be one of us again! 
You "schooling" has been splen-did, that I know, and you are better able to meet the future then you. 
could have been, if Fate had not given you this chance to see an entirely different side of life.- you are going to be so awfully welcome! Now I am so awfully welcome! Now I am counting the days till you arrive! 
We are looking for Uncle Jim and Aunt Lora for a visit, may be tomorrow, and I believe they will stay several days. The girls are all cleaning the house for me, getting dinner, mowing the grass and what not, as I am having one of my sweet headaches at pre-

